<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2187">
Your task is to calculate the number of valid bracket sequences of length $n$ when a <i>prefix</i> of the sequence is given.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
The second line has a string of $k$ characters: the prefix of the sequence.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the number of sequences modulo $10^9+7$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le k \le n \le 10^6$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>6<br />
(()</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>2</code><br />
<br />
Explanation: There are two possible sequences: <code>(())()</code> and <code>(()())</code>.    </div>
